main event: A sighting of a round object that was brighter than a star occurred in Kirkland, Washington on July 23, 1955.
interesting points: The object was observed for 30 minutes without any sound,The object moved up and down as well as sideways,Initial positional data indicated the object was stationary,The sighting was reported to possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon; insufficient data for evaluation was noted,The object was noted to be located at an elevation of 150 degrees.
sighted object: a round object brighter than a star
witness description: Mr. and Mrs. from Kirkland, Washington
